TD -1.050000E-004 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 4.368000E-001 1.052000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC POLYCARB  (Polycarbonate, bisphenol-A based, optical grade)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: N. Sultanova, S. Kasarova, I. Nikolov, "Dispersion Properties of
CC         Optical Polymers," Acta Physica Polonica A 116, 585-587 (2009).
CC         Single-term Sellmeier fit over 0.4368 - 1.052 um at 293 K.
CC         Coefficients from refractiveindex.info Sultanova 2009 PC page.
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Sultanova 2009), wavelength in micrometers:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 1.4182 * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.021304)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 (formula type 2):
CC   K1 = 1.4182, L1 = 0.021304, K2 = L2 = K3 = L3 = 0
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 1.59959
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 1.58472   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 1.57863
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 27.9
CC
CC Note: Handbook PC values are often nd=1.585 / Vd=30. As with PMMA, the
CC single-term fit underpredicts Vd. Acceptable for stock-lens import.
CC
CC Density 1.20 g/cm^3; TCE approx 67 ppm/K; dn/dT approx -1.07e-4 /K.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

