CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC SAPPHIRE  (single-crystal Al2O3, ordinary ray)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: I.H. Malitson and M.J. Dodge, "Refractive Index and Birefringence
CC         of Synthetic Sapphire," J. Opt. Soc. Am. 62, 1405A (1972).
CC         Single-crystal Al2O3, room temperature, ordinary-ray index n_o.
CC
CC Sapphire is uniaxial (n_o != n_e); the ordinary-ray index is used for
CC stock optics where the c-axis is normal to the optical axis (typical
CC for c-cut and a-cut windows / lenses sold as "isotropic sapphire").
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Malitson & Dodge 1972), wavelength in micrometers:
CC   n_o^2 - 1 = 1.4313493  * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.0726631^2)
CC             + 0.65054713 * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.1193242^2)
CC             + 5.3414021  * L^2 / (L^2 - 18.028251^2)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 (formula type 2) stores L_i in squared form (um^2):
CC   L1 = 0.0726631^2  = 0.005279927
CC   L2 = 0.1193242^2  = 0.014238265
CC   L3 = 18.028251^2  = 325.017834
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n_o approx 1.7747
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n_o approx 1.7682    <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n_o approx 1.7651
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 78
CC
CC Validity (Malitson & Dodge 1972): 0.265 - 5.5 um.
CC Density 3.98 g/cm^3; TCE approx 6.7 ppm/K (parallel c-axis), 5.0 ppm/K
CC (perpendicular c-axis); dn/dT approx +1.3e-5 /K at room temperature visible.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

